    "John T. Carroll": ").130\nA history of law-keeping notwithstanding, this man has come to Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` on a\nquest, hinting that he already realizes something is missing from his religious-\nethical practice. Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` acknowledges the deficiency\u2014\u201cOne thing is still lacking\nin you\u201d\u2014and names it in radical terms: \u201cSell everything you have and distribute\n[the proceeds] to the poor, and you will have a treasure in heaven\u2014and come,\nfollow me!\u201d (\n21. Ministry Continues as Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Journeys to Jerusalem\n365\ngain entrance into the domain that God rules (",
