    "John T. Carroll": ").131 Ironic wit here: what is lacking is, paradoxically, an\nincapacity to release abundance! A member of the social elite hears a challenge\nto redistribute wealth to those who lack economic resources.132 Only now, in\ndescribing the quester\u2019s reaction, does the narrator disclose that the man is\n\u201cextremely wealthy\u201d (\nv. 22 between \u201cone thing lacking\u201d and\nits unpacking in two elements (give away to benefit the poor and follow Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`); however, the two\nactions (disinvest wealth to reinvest in the poor and answer a call to follow) are being presented as\none coordinated response to a summons to discipleship. The phrasing of",
