    "John Trapp": "That ye may be accounted worthy ] Great is the emphasis of this word, \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1\u03be\u03b9\u03c9\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5 (saith learned Beza), for it gives us to understand that we owe all to the free election of God, who loved us first, and so accepted us for worthy, #Re 3:4 .\nVer.\n36. That ye may be accounted worthy] Great is the emphasis of this word, \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1\u03be\u03b9\u03c9\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5 (saith learned Beza), for it gives us to understand that we owe all to the free election of God, who loved [v_Rev_3_4] us first, and so accepted us for worthy, #Re 3:"
